phant tending to give him away (since some were ordered from the back of a comic book), Loudmouse blowing his cover when staking out the villain, Undercover Elephant being unable to avoid the exploding messages (a-la ''[[Mission: Impossible (1966 TV series)|Mission Impossible]]'') being sent to him by his Chief (voiced by [[Michael Bell (actor)|Michael Bell]]), and to resist [[peanut]]s.\n\n====Episodes====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:95%; background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#32CD32; width:30px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#32CD32\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#32CD32; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.1\n| Title = The Sneaky Sheik\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|10}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.2\n| Title = Baron Von Rippemoff\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|17}}\n| ShortSummary = The nation's most sophisticated experimental aircraft known as X-3000 has been stolen by a notorious spy named Baron Von Rippemoff. Undercover Elephant and Loudmouse head to a private airfield in North Africa in order to retrieve the X-3000 and apprehend Baron Von Rippemoff.\n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.3\n| Title = The Moanin' Lisa\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|24}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.4\n| Title = Pain in the Brain\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|1}}\n| ShortSummary = The pair must protect Dr. Von Brain from a rival mad scientist intending to kidnap him.\n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.5\n| Title = The Great Hospital Hassle\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|8}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.6\n| Title = Latin Losers\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|15}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 32CD32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = U.