[Lennie Weinrib]]), and cheerleaders Sheena the Lioness (voiced by [[Ginny McSwain]]) and Zelda the [[Ostrich]] (voiced by [[Susan Silo]]) attempt schemes to get into the spotlight.\n\n====Episodes====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:30px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#B11030\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.1\n| Title = The Blue Kangaroo\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|10}}\n| ShortSummary = King and his group come across an escaped Blue Kangaroo that is being pursued by a hunter named Hunter Hunter.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.2\n| Title = The First King on Mars\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|17}}\n| ShortSummary = King and his group come up with a plan to go to [[Mars]]. One of their attempts lands them near the movie set of a [[Martian]] movie.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.3\n| Title = The Riverbed 5000\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|9|24}}\n| ShortSummary = King and his group participate on a car race to win $5000 and a kiss from the actress Raquel Wrench.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.4\n| Title = Surf's Up\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|1}}\n| ShortSummary = King and his group go to Tempest Beach for a picnic. After Skids works on a customized surfboard, Big H enters its surfing competition.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.5\n| Title = The King and His Jokers\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|8}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.6\n| Title = Hot Gold Fever\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|15}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = H.7\n| Title = The Carnival Caper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1977|10|22}}\