09]]]</sup> || [[Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Transport]] || [[State Post Bureau]]  || [[China Post]] Group<br>[[Hong Kong]]: [[Hongkong Post]]<br>[[Macao]]: [[CTT (Macau)|Correios de Macau]]\n|-\n| {{Flag|Colombia}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || [[Ministry of Information Technologies and Communications]] || [[Regulatory Commission of Communications]] (CRC) and [[Superintendency of Industry and Commerce]] (SIC)<ref name=\"REGCOL\">{{cite web|last=4-72|title=Regulatory authorities of the Colombian postal service|url=http://4-72.com.co/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=97&Itemid=194|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> || [[Servicios Postales Nacionales]] S.A. (4-72)\n|-\n| {{Flag|Comoros}} ||  ||  || [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 Nationale des Postes et des Services Financiers]]<ref name=\"UPU Member Countries\" />\n|-\n| {{Flag|Republic of the Congo}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications || Directorate General of the Central Posts and Telecommunications Administration || [[Congo Posts and Savings Company]] (SOPECO)\n|-\n| {{Flag|Costa Rica}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || None || [[Autoridad Reguladora de Servicios P\u00fablicos]] (ARESEP) || [[Correos de Costa Rica]] SA\n|-\n| {{Flag|Croatia}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || [[Ministry of the Sea, Tourism, Transport and Development]] || [[Postal Services Council]] || HP-[[Hrvatska po\u0161ta]] d.d\n|-\n| {{Flag|Cuba}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || [[Ministry of Informatics and Communications]] || None || [[Empresa de Correos de Cuba]]\n|-\n| {{Flag|Cura\u00e7ao}}<ref name=defacto1 group=N>now called Aruba, Cura\u00e7ao and Sint Maarten</ref> ||  ||  || [[Cpost International]]\n|-\n| {{Flag|Cyprus}}<sup>[[#cite note-UPU-0|[2009]]]</sup> || [[Ministry of Communications and Public Works]] || [[Commissioner of Telecommunications and Postal Regulation]] || [[Cyprus Postal Services|Department of Posta